VisionNex Kiosk - Quick Setup & Run Guide
1. Prerequisites

Make sure your system has:

XAMPP (PHP 8.x + MySQL + Apache)

Modern browser (Chrome recommended)

Camera for face recognition

2. Folder Setup

Copy the project to your local server:

C:\xampp\htdocs\php_project_copy\


Folder structure must remain exactly the same:

php_project_copy/
├─ attendance_project/
│  ├─ backend_php/api/
│  │     ├─ face_recognition.php
│  │     └─ classes.php
│  └─ kiosk/
│        └─ kiosk.js
├─ dashboard/uploads/students/
├─ dashboard/admin/uploads/teachers/
├─ public/config/db.php


Do NOT rename folders or files — API paths depend on these.

3. Database Setup

Open phpmyadmin in browser.

Create a database (e.g., attendance_system).

Import your existing database dump (students, teachers, classes, attendance).

Update public/config/db.php with correct database name and credentials.

4. Running the Kiosk

Start Apache and MySQL in XAMPP.

Open kiosk page in browser:

http://localhost/php_project_copy/attendance_project/kiosk/kiosk.html


Allow camera access.

Click Start Camera.

System auto-detects faces (if auto-capture is enabled) or click Capture manually.

5. Moving/Editing on Another Device

Copy entire folder to new htdocs location.

Import database into local MySQL.

Update db.php if credentials differ.

Start XAMPP, open kiosk page, allow camera.

Do NOT rename folders/files or open kiosk as file:// — always use localhost.

6. Quick Commands / Tips

Start Apache & MySQL: XAMPP Control Panel

Check API: Open http://localhost/php_project_copy/attendance_project/backend_php/api/face_recognition.php?action=faces

Clear stats/settings: Clear localStorage in browser console

Restart camera: Click Stop Camera → Start Camera

7. Common Issues
Problem	Fix
API Offline / 404	Check folder structure and API file paths
Recognition Failed	Ensure database has correct images & data
Camera not working	Allow camera in browser; ensure no other apps are using it